105static const char* stringForRareDataUseType(NodeRareData::UseType useType)
106{
107 switch (useType) {
108 case NodeRareData::UseType::NodeList:
109 return "NodeList";
110 case NodeRareData::UseType::MutationObserver:
111 return "MutationObserver";
112 case NodeRareData::UseType::TabIndex:
113 return "TabIndex";
114 case NodeRareData::UseType::MinimumSize:
115 return "MinimumSize";
116 case NodeRareData::UseType::ScrollingPosition:
117 return "ScrollingPosition";
118 case NodeRareData::UseType::ComputedStyle:
119 return "ComputedStyle";
120 case NodeRareData::UseType::Dataset:
121 return "Dataset";
122 case NodeRareData::UseType::ClassList:
123 return "ClassList";
124 case NodeRareData::UseType::ShadowRoot:
125 return "ShadowRoot";
126 case NodeRareData::UseType::CustomElementQueue:
127 return "CustomElementQueue";
128 case NodeRareData::UseType::AttributeMap:
129 return "AttributeMap";
130 case NodeRareData::UseType::InteractionObserver:
131 return "InteractionObserver";
132 case NodeRareData::UseType::ResizeObserver:
133 return "ResizeObserver";
134 case NodeRareData::UseType::Animations:
135 return "Animations";
136 case NodeRareData::UseType::PseudoElements:
137 return "PseudoElements";
138 case NodeRareData::UseType::StyleMap:
139 return "StyleMap";
140 case NodeRareData::UseType::PartList:
141 return "PartList";
142 case NodeRareData::UseType::PartNames:
143 return "PartNames";
144 }
145 return nullptr;
146}

150void Node::dumpStatistics()
151{
152#if DUMP_NODE_STATISTICS
153 size_t nodesWithRareData = 0;
154
155 size_t elementNodes = 0;
156 size_t attrNodes = 0;
157 size_t textNodes = 0;
158 size_t cdataNodes = 0;
159 size_t commentNodes = 0;
160 size_t piNodes = 0;
161 size_t documentNodes = 0;
162 size_t docTypeNodes = 0;
163 size_t fragmentNodes = 0;
164 size_t shadowRootNodes = 0;
165
166 HashMap<String, size_t> perTagCount;
167
168 size_t attributes = 0;
169 size_t attributesWithAttr = 0;
170 size_t elementsWithAttributeStorage = 0;
171 size_t elementsWithRareData = 0;
172 size_t elementsWithNamedNodeMap = 0;
173
174 HashMap<uint16_t, size_t> rareDataSingleUseTypeCounts;
175 size_t mixedRareDataUseCount = 0;
176
177 for (auto& node : liveNodeSet()) {
178 if (node.hasRareData()) {
179 ++nodesWithRareData;
180 if (is<Element>(node)) {
181 ++elementsWithRareData;
182 if (downcast<Element>(node).hasNamedNodeMap())
183 ++elementsWithNamedNodeMap;
184 }
185 auto* rareData = node.rareData();
186 auto useTypes = is<Element>(node) ? static_cast<ElementRareData*>(rareData)->useTypes() : rareData->useTypes();
187 unsigned useTypeCount = 0;
188 for (auto type : useTypes) {
189 UNUSED_PARAM(type);
190 useTypeCount++;
191 }
192 if (useTypeCount == 1) {
193 auto result = rareDataSingleUseTypeCounts.add(static_cast<uint16_t>(*useTypes.begin()), 0);
194 result.iterator->value++;
195 } else
196 mixedRareDataUseCount++;
197 }
198
199 switch (node.nodeType()) {
200 case ELEMENT_NODE: {
201 ++elementNodes;
202
203 // Tag stats
204 Element& element = downcast<Element>(node);
205 HashMap<String, size_t>::AddResult result = perTagCount.add(element.tagName(), 1);
206 if (!result.isNewEntry)
207 result.iterator->value++;
208
209 if (const ElementData* elementData = element.elementData()) {
210 unsigned length = elementData->length();
211 attributes += length;
212 ++elementsWithAttributeStorage;
213 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
214 const Attribute& attr = elementData->attributeAt(i);
215 if (element.attrIfExists(attr.name()))
216 ++attributesWithAttr;
217 }
218 }
219 break;
220 }
221 case ATTRIBUTE_NODE: {
222 ++attrNodes;
223 break;
224 }
225 case TEXT_NODE: {
226 ++textNodes;
227 break;
228 }
229 case CDATA_SECTION_NODE: {
230 ++cdataNodes;
231 break;
232 }
233 case PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE: {
234 ++piNodes;
235 break;
236 }
237 case COMMENT_NODE: {
238 ++commentNodes;
239 break;
240 }
241 case DOCUMENT_NODE: {
242 ++documentNodes;
243 break;
244 }
245 case DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE: {
246 ++docTypeNodes;
247 break;
248 }
249 case DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE: {
250 if (node.isShadowRoot())
251 ++shadowRootNodes;
252 else
253 ++fragmentNodes;
254 break;
255 }
256 }
257 }
258
259 printf("Number of Nodes: %d\n\n", liveNodeSet().computeSize());
260 printf("Number of Nodes with RareData: %zu\n", nodesWithRareData);
261 printf(" Mixed use: %zu\n", mixedRareDataUseCount);
262 for (auto it : rareDataSingleUseTypeCounts)
263 printf(" %s: %zu\n", stringForRareDataUseType(static_cast<NodeRareData::UseType>(it.key)), it.value);
264 printf("\n");
265
266
267 printf("NodeType distribution:\n");
268 printf(" Number of Element nodes: %zu\n", elementNodes);
269 printf(" Number of Attribute nodes: %zu\n", attrNodes);
270 printf(" Number of Text nodes: %zu\n", textNodes);
271 printf(" Number of CDATASection nodes: %zu\n", cdataNodes);
272 printf(" Number of Comment nodes: %zu\n", commentNodes);
273 printf(" Number of ProcessingInstruction nodes: %zu\n", piNodes);
274 printf(" Number of Document nodes: %zu\n", documentNodes);
275 printf(" Number of DocumentType nodes: %zu\n", docTypeNodes);
276 printf(" Number of DocumentFragment nodes: %zu\n", fragmentNodes);
277 printf(" Number of ShadowRoot nodes: %zu\n", shadowRootNodes);
278
279 printf("Element tag name distibution:\n");
280 for (auto& stringSizePair : perTagCount)
281 printf(" Number of <%s> tags: %zu\n", stringSizePair.key.utf8().data(), stringSizePair.value);
282
283 printf("Attributes:\n");
284 printf(" Number of Attributes (non-Node and Node): %zu [%zu]\n", attributes, sizeof(Attribute));
285 printf(" Number of Attributes with an Attr: %zu\n", attributesWithAttr);
286 printf(" Number of Elements with attribute storage: %zu [%zu]\n", elementsWithAttributeStorage, sizeof(ElementData));
287 printf(" Number of Elements with RareData: %zu\n", elementsWithRareData);
288 printf(" Number of Elements with NamedNodeMap: %zu [%zu]\n", elementsWithNamedNodeMap, sizeof(NamedNodeMap));
289#endif
290}

319void Node::trackForDebugging()
320{
321#ifndef NDEBUG
322 if (shouldIgnoreLeaks)
323 ignoreSet().add(*this);
324 else
325 nodeCounter.increment();
326#endif
327
328#if DUMP_NODE_STATISTICS
329 liveNodeSet().add(*this);

333Node::Node(Document& document, ConstructionType type)
334 : m_nodeFlags(type)
335 , m_treeScope(&document)
336{
337 ASSERT(isMainThread());
338
339 document.incrementReferencingNodeCount();
340
341#if !defined(NDEBUG) || (defined(DUMP_NODE_STATISTICS) && DUMP_NODE_STATISTICS)
342 trackForDebugging();
343#endif
344}
345
346Node::~Node()
347{
348 ASSERT(isMainThread());
349 ASSERT(m_refCountAndParentBit == s_refCountIncrement);
350 ASSERT(m_deletionHasBegun);
351 ASSERT(!m_adoptionIsRequired);
352
353 InspectorInstrumentation::willDestroyDOMNode(*this);
354
355#ifndef NDEBUG
356 if (!ignoreSet().remove(*this))
357 nodeCounter.decrement();
358#endif
359
360#if DUMP_NODE_STATISTICS
361 liveNodeSet().remove(*this);
362#endif
363
364 RELEASE_ASSERT(!renderer());
365 ASSERT(!parentNode());
366 ASSERT(!m_previous);
367 ASSERT(!m_next);
368
369 if (hasRareData())
370 clearRareData();
371
372 auto* textManipulationController = document().textManipulationControllerIfExists();
373 if (UNLIKELY(textManipulationController))
374 textManipulationController->removeNode(*this);
375
376 if (!isContainerNode())
377 willBeDeletedFrom(document());
378
379 if (hasEventTargetData())
380 clearEventTargetData();
381
382 document().decrementReferencingNodeCount();
383
384#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS) && PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY) && (ASSERT_ENABLED || ENABLE(SECURITY_ASSERTIONS))
385 for (auto* document : Document::allDocuments()) {
386 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!document->touchEventListenersContain(*this));
387 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!document->touchEventHandlersContain(*this));
388 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!document->touchEventTargetsContain(*this));
389 }
390#endif
391}
392
393void Node::willBeDeletedFrom(Document& document)
394{
395 if (hasEventTargetData()) {
396 document.didRemoveWheelEventHandler(*this, EventHandlerRemoval::All);
397#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
398#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
399 document.removeTouchEventListener(*this, EventHandlerRemoval::All);
400#endif
401 document.didRemoveTouchEventHandler(*this, EventHandlerRemoval::All);
402#endif
403 }
404
405#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS) && PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
406 document.removeTouchEventHandler(*this, EventHandlerRemoval::All);
407#endif
408
409 if (auto* cache = document.existingAXObjectCache())
410 cache->remove(*this);
411}

413void Node::materializeRareData()
414{
415 if (is<Element>(*this))
416 m_rareDataWithBitfields.setPointer(std::unique_ptr<NodeRareData, NodeRareDataDeleter>(new ElementRareData));
417 else
418 m_rareDataWithBitfields.setPointer(std::unique_ptr<NodeRareData, NodeRareDataDeleter>(new NodeRareData));
419}
420
421inline void Node::NodeRareDataDeleter::operator()(NodeRareData* rareData) const
422{
423 if (rareData->isElementRareData())
424 delete static_cast<ElementRareData*>(rareData);
425 else
426 delete static_cast<NodeRareData*>(rareData);
427}

429void Node::clearRareData()
430{
431 ASSERT(hasRareData());
432 ASSERT(!transientMutationObserverRegistry() || transientMutationObserverRegistry()->isEmpty());
433
434 m_rareDataWithBitfields.setPointer(nullptr);
435}

514static HashSet<RefPtr<Node>> nodeSetPreTransformedFromNodeOrStringVector(const Vector<NodeOrString>& vector)
515{
516 HashSet<RefPtr<Node>> nodeSet;
517 for (const auto& variant : vector) {
518 WTF::switchOn(variant,
519 [&] (const RefPtr<Node>& node) { nodeSet.add(const_cast<Node*>(node.get())); },
520 [] (const String&) { }
521 );
522 }
523 return nodeSet;
524}
525
526static RefPtr<Node> firstPrecedingSiblingNotInNodeSet(Node& context, const HashSet<RefPtr<Node>>& nodeSet)
527{
528 for (auto* sibling = context.previousSibling(); sibling; sibling = sibling->previousSibling()) {
529 if (!nodeSet.contains(sibling))
530 return sibling;
531 }
532 return nullptr;
533}
534
535static RefPtr<Node> firstFollowingSiblingNotInNodeSet(Node& context, const HashSet<RefPtr<Node>>& nodeSet)
536{
537 for (auto* sibling = context.nextSibling(); sibling; sibling = sibling->nextSibling()) {
538 if (!nodeSet.contains(sibling))
539 return sibling;
540 }
541 return nullptr;
542}

544ExceptionOr<RefPtr<Node>> Node::convertNodesOrStringsIntoNode(Vector<NodeOrString>&& nodeOrStringVector)
545{
546 if (nodeOrStringVector.isEmpty())
547 return nullptr;
548
549 Vector<Ref<Node>> nodes;
550 nodes.reserveInitialCapacity(nodeOrStringVector.size());
551 for (auto& variant : nodeOrStringVector) {
552 WTF::switchOn(variant,
553 [&](RefPtr<Node>& node) { nodes.uncheckedAppend(*node.get()); },
554 [&](String& string) { nodes.uncheckedAppend(Text::create(document(), string)); }
555 );
556 }
557
558 if (nodes.size() == 1)
559 return RefPtr<Node> { WTFMove(nodes.first()) };
560
561 auto nodeToReturn = DocumentFragment::create(document());
562 for (auto& node : nodes) {
563 auto appendResult = nodeToReturn->appendChild(node);
564 if (appendResult.hasException())
565 return appendResult.releaseException();
566 }
567 return RefPtr<Node> { WTFMove(nodeToReturn) };
568}
569
570ExceptionOr<void> Node::before(Vector<NodeOrString>&& nodeOrStringVector)
571{
572 RefPtr<ContainerNode> parent = parentNode();
573 if (!parent)
574 return { };
575
576 auto nodeSet = nodeSetPreTransformedFromNodeOrStringVector(nodeOrStringVector);
577 auto viablePreviousSibling = firstPrecedingSiblingNotInNodeSet(*this, nodeSet);
578
579 auto result = convertNodesOrStringsIntoNode(WTFMove(nodeOrStringVector));
580 if (result.hasException())
581 return result.releaseException();
582 auto node = result.releaseReturnValue();
583 if (!node)
584 return { };
585
586 if (viablePreviousSibling)
587 viablePreviousSibling = viablePreviousSibling->nextSibling();
588 else
589 viablePreviousSibling = parent->firstChild();
590
591 return parent->insertBefore(*node, viablePreviousSibling.get());
592}
593
594ExceptionOr<void> Node::after(Vector<NodeOrString>&& nodeOrStringVector)
595{
596 RefPtr<ContainerNode> parent = parentNode();
597 if (!parent)
598 return { };
599
600 auto nodeSet = nodeSetPreTransformedFromNodeOrStringVector(nodeOrStringVector);
601 auto viableNextSibling = firstFollowingSiblingNotInNodeSet(*this, nodeSet);
602
603 auto result = convertNodesOrStringsIntoNode(WTFMove(nodeOrStringVector));
604 if (result.hasException())
605 return result.releaseException();
606 auto node = result.releaseReturnValue();
607 if (!node)
608 return { };
609
610 return parent->insertBefore(*node, viableNextSibling.get());
611}
612
613ExceptionOr<void> Node::replaceWith(Vector<NodeOrString>&& nodeOrStringVector)
614{
615 RefPtr<ContainerNode> parent = parentNode();
616 if (!parent)
617 return { };
618
619 auto nodeSet = nodeSetPreTransformedFromNodeOrStringVector(nodeOrStringVector);
620 auto viableNextSibling = firstFollowingSiblingNotInNodeSet(*this, nodeSet);
621
622 auto result = convertNodesOrStringsIntoNode(WTFMove(nodeOrStringVector));
623 if (result.hasException())
624 return result.releaseException();
625
626 if (parentNode() == parent) {
627 if (auto node = result.releaseReturnValue())
628 return parent->replaceChild(*node, *this);
629 return parent->removeChild(*this);
630 }
631
632 if (auto node = result.releaseReturnValue())
633 return parent->insertBefore(*node, viableNextSibling.get());
634 return { };
635}
636
637ExceptionOr<void> Node::remove()
638{
639 auto* parent = parentNode();
640 if (!parent)
641 return { };
642 return parent->removeChild(*this);
643}

645void Node::normalize()
646{
647 // Go through the subtree beneath us, normalizing all nodes. This means that
648 // any two adjacent text nodes are merged and any empty text nodes are removed.
649
650 RefPtr<Node> node = this;
651 while (Node* firstChild = node->firstChild())
652 node = firstChild;
653 while (node) {
654 NodeType type = node->nodeType();
655 if (type == ELEMENT_NODE)
656 downcast<Element>(*node).normalizeAttributes();
657
658 if (node == this)
659 break;
660
661 if (type != TEXT_NODE) {
662 node = NodeTraversal::nextPostOrder(*node);
663 continue;
664 }
665
666 RefPtr<Text> text = downcast<Text>(node.get());
667
668 // Remove empty text nodes.
669 if (!text->length()) {
670 // Care must be taken to get the next node before removing the current node.
671 node = NodeTraversal::nextPostOrder(*node);
672 text->remove();
673 continue;
674 }
675
676 // Merge text nodes.
677 while (Node* nextSibling = node->nextSibling()) {
678 if (nextSibling->nodeType() != TEXT_NODE)
679 break;
680 Ref<Text> nextText = downcast<Text>(*nextSibling);
681
682 // Remove empty text nodes.
683 if (!nextText->length()) {
684 nextText->remove();
685 continue;
686 }
687
688 // Both non-empty text nodes. Merge them.
689 unsigned offset = text->length();
690
691 // Update start/end for any affected Ranges before appendData since modifying contents might trigger mutation events that modify ordering.
692 document().textNodesMerged(nextText, offset);
693
694 // FIXME: DOM spec requires contents to be replaced all at once (see https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#dom-node-normalize).
695 // Appending once per sibling may trigger mutation events too many times.
696 text->appendData(nextText->data());
697 nextText->remove();
698 }
699
700 node = NodeTraversal::nextPostOrder(*node);
701 }
702}

717ExceptionOr<void> Node::setPrefix(const AtomString&)
718{
719 // The spec says that for nodes other than elements and attributes, prefix is always null.
720 // It does not say what to do when the user tries to set the prefix on another type of
721 // node, however Mozilla throws a NamespaceError exception.
722 return Exception { NamespaceError };
723}

751static Node::Editability computeEditabilityFromComputedStyle(const Node& startNode, Node::UserSelectAllTreatment treatment)
752{
753 // Ideally we'd call ASSERT(!needsStyleRecalc()) here, but
754 // ContainerNode::setFocus() calls invalidateStyleForSubtree(), so the assertion
755 // would fire in the middle of Document::setFocusedElement().
756
757 for (const Node* node = &startNode; node; node = node->parentNode()) {
758 auto* style = node->isDocumentNode() ? node->renderStyle() : const_cast<Node*>(node)->computedStyle();
759 if (!style)
760 continue;
761 if (style->display() == DisplayType::None)
762 continue;
763 // Elements with user-select: all style are considered atomic
764 // therefore non editable.
765 if (treatment == Node::UserSelectAllIsAlwaysNonEditable && style->userSelect() == UserSelect::All)
766 return Node::Editability::ReadOnly;
767 switch (style->userModify()) {
768 case UserModify::ReadOnly:
769 return Node::Editability::ReadOnly;
770 case UserModify::ReadWrite:
771 return Node::Editability::CanEditRichly;
772 case UserModify::ReadWritePlaintextOnly:
773 return Node::Editability::CanEditPlainText;
774 }
775 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
776 return Node::Editability::ReadOnly;
777 }
778 return Node::Editability::ReadOnly;
779}
780
781Node::Editability Node::computeEditability(UserSelectAllTreatment treatment, ShouldUpdateStyle shouldUpdateStyle) const
782{
783 if (!document().hasLivingRenderTree() || isPseudoElement())
784 return Editability::ReadOnly;
785
786 if (isInShadowTree())
787 return HTMLElement::editabilityFromContentEditableAttr(*this);
788
789 if (document().frame() && document().frame()->page() && document().frame()->page()->isEditable())
790 return Editability::CanEditRichly;
791
792 if (shouldUpdateStyle == ShouldUpdateStyle::Update && document().needsStyleRecalc()) {
793 if (!document().usesStyleBasedEditability())
794 return HTMLElement::editabilityFromContentEditableAttr(*this);
795 document().updateStyleIfNeeded();
796 }
797 return computeEditabilityFromComputedStyle(*this, treatment);
798}

812LayoutRect Node::renderRect(bool* isReplaced)
813{
814 RenderObject* hitRenderer = this->renderer();
815 if (!hitRenderer && is<HTMLAreaElement>(*this)) {
816 auto& area = downcast<HTMLAreaElement>(*this);
817 if (auto* imageElement = area.imageElement())
818 hitRenderer = imageElement->renderer();
819 }
820 RenderObject* renderer = hitRenderer;
821 while (renderer && !renderer->isBody() && !renderer->isDocumentElementRenderer()) {
822 if (renderer->isRenderBlock() || renderer->isInlineBlockOrInlineTable() || renderer->isReplaced()) {
823 *isReplaced = renderer->isReplaced();
824 return renderer->absoluteBoundingBoxRect();
825 }
826 renderer = renderer->parent();
827 }
828 return LayoutRect();
829}

841void Node::adjustStyleValidity(Style::Validity validity, Style::InvalidationMode mode)
842{
843 if (validity > styleValidity()) {
844 auto bitfields = styleBitfields();
845 bitfields.setStyleValidity(validity);
846 setStyleBitfields(bitfields);
847 }
848 if (mode == Style::InvalidationMode::RecompositeLayer)
849 setStyleFlag(NodeStyleFlag::StyleResolutionShouldRecompositeLayer);
850}
851
852inline void Node::updateAncestorsForStyleRecalc()
853{
854 auto composedAncestors = composedTreeAncestors(*this);
855 auto it = composedAncestors.begin();
856 auto end = composedAncestors.end();
857 if (it != end) {
858 it->setDirectChildNeedsStyleRecalc();
859
860 for (; it != end; ++it) {
861 // Iterator skips over shadow roots.
862 if (auto* shadowRoot = it->shadowRoot())
863 shadowRoot->setChildNeedsStyleRecalc();
864 if (it->childNeedsStyleRecalc())
865 break;
866 it->setChildNeedsStyleRecalc();
867 }
868 }
869
870 auto* documentElement = document().documentElement();
871 if (!documentElement)
872 return;
873 if (!documentElement->childNeedsStyleRecalc() && !documentElement->needsStyleRecalc())
874 return;
875 document().setChildNeedsStyleRecalc();
876 document().scheduleStyleRecalc();
877}
878
879void Node::invalidateStyle(Style::Validity validity, Style::InvalidationMode mode)
880{
881 ASSERT(validity != Style::Validity::Valid);
882 if (!inRenderedDocument())
883 return;
884
885 // FIXME: This should eventually be an ASSERT.
886 if (document().inRenderTreeUpdate())
887 return;
888
889 // FIXME: This should be set on all descendants in case of a subtree invalidation.
890 setNodeFlag(NodeFlag::IsComputedStyleInvalidFlag);
891
892 // FIXME: Why the second condition?
893 bool markAncestors = styleValidity() == Style::Validity::Valid || validity == Style::Validity::SubtreeAndRenderersInvalid;
894
895 adjustStyleValidity(validity, mode);
896
897 if (markAncestors)
898 updateAncestorsForStyleRecalc();
899}

998ExceptionOr<void> Node::checkSetPrefix(const AtomString& prefix)
999{
1000 // Perform error checking as required by spec for setting Node.prefix. Used by
1001 // Element::setPrefix() and Attr::setPrefix()
1002
1003 if (!prefix.isEmpty() && !Document::isValidName(prefix))
1004 return Exception { InvalidCharacterError };
1005
1006 // FIXME: Raise NamespaceError if prefix is malformed per the Namespaces in XML specification.
1007
1008 auto& namespaceURI = this->namespaceURI();
1009 if (namespaceURI.isEmpty() && !prefix.isEmpty())
1010 return Exception { NamespaceError };
1011 if (prefix == xmlAtom() && namespaceURI != XMLNames::xmlNamespaceURI)
1012 return Exception { NamespaceError };
1013
1014 // Attribute-specific checks are in Attr::setPrefix().
1015
1016 return { };
1017}

1019bool Node::isDescendantOf(const Node& other) const
1020{
1021 // Return true if other is an ancestor of this.
1022 if (other.isDocumentNode())
1023 return &treeScope().rootNode() == &other && !isDocumentNode() && isConnected();
1024 if (!other.hasChildNodes() || isConnected() != other.isConnected())
1025 return false;
1026 for (auto ancestor = parentNode(); ancestor; ancestor = ancestor->parentNode()) {
1027 if (ancestor == &other)
1028 return true;
1029 }
1030 return false;
1031}

1033bool Node::isDescendantOrShadowDescendantOf(const Node& other) const
1034{
1035 if (isDescendantOf(other))
1036 return true;
1037
1038 for (auto host = shadowHost(); host; host = host->shadowHost()) {
1039 if (other.contains(*host))
1040 return true;
1041 }
1042
1043 return false;
1044}

1154static bool isClosedShadowHiddenUsingSpecDefinition(const Node& A, const Node& B)
1155{
1156 return A.isInShadowTree()
1157 && !A.rootNode().containsIncludingShadowDOM(&B)
1158 && (A.containingShadowRoot()->mode() != ShadowRootMode::Open || isClosedShadowHiddenUsingSpecDefinition(*A.shadowHost(), B));

1161
1162// http://w3c.github.io/webcomponents/spec/shadow/#dfn-unclosed-node
1163bool Node::isClosedShadowHidden(const Node& otherNode) const
1164{
1165 // Use Vector instead of HashSet since we expect the number of ancestor tree scopes to be small.
1166 Vector<TreeScope*, 8> ancestorScopesOfThisNode;
1167
1168 for (auto* scope = &treeScope(); scope; scope = scope->parentTreeScope())
1169 ancestorScopesOfThisNode.append(scope);
1170
1171 for (auto* treeScopeThatCanAccessOtherNode = &otherNode.treeScope(); treeScopeThatCanAccessOtherNode; treeScopeThatCanAccessOtherNode = treeScopeThatCanAccessOtherNode->parentTreeScope()) {
1172 for (auto* scope : ancestorScopesOfThisNode) {
1173 if (scope == treeScopeThatCanAccessOtherNode) {
1174 ASSERT(!isClosedShadowHiddenUsingSpecDefinition(otherNode, *this));
1175 return false; // treeScopeThatCanAccessOtherNode is a shadow-including inclusive ancestor of this node.
1176 }
1177 }
1178 auto& root = treeScopeThatCanAccessOtherNode->rootNode();
1179 if (is<ShadowRoot>(root) && downcast<ShadowRoot>(root).mode() != ShadowRootMode::Open)
1180 break;
1181 }
1182
1183 ASSERT(isClosedShadowHiddenUsingSpecDefinition(otherNode, *this));
1184 return true;
1185}

1356bool Node::isEqualNode(Node* other) const
1357{
1358 if (!other)
1359 return false;
1360
1361 NodeType nodeType = this->nodeType();
1362 if (nodeType != other->nodeType())
1363 return false;
1364
1365 switch (nodeType) {
1366 case Node::DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE: {
1367 auto& thisDocType = downcast<DocumentType>(*this);
1368 auto& otherDocType = downcast<DocumentType>(*other);
1369 if (thisDocType.name() != otherDocType.name())
1370 return false;
1371 if (thisDocType.publicId() != otherDocType.publicId())
1372 return false;
1373 if (thisDocType.systemId() != otherDocType.systemId())
1374 return false;
1375 break;
1376 }
1377 case Node::ELEMENT_NODE: {
1378 auto& thisElement = downcast<Element>(*this);
1379 auto& otherElement = downcast<Element>(*other);
1380 if (thisElement.tagQName() != otherElement.tagQName())
1381 return false;
1382 if (!thisElement.hasEquivalentAttributes(otherElement))
1383 return false;
1384 break;
1385 }
1386 case Node::PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE: {
1387 auto& thisProcessingInstruction = downcast<ProcessingInstruction>(*this);
1388 auto& otherProcessingInstruction = downcast<ProcessingInstruction>(*other);
1389 if (thisProcessingInstruction.target() != otherProcessingInstruction.target())
1390 return false;
1391 if (thisProcessingInstruction.data() != otherProcessingInstruction.data())
1392 return false;
1393 break;
1394 }
1395 case Node::CDATA_SECTION_NODE:
1396 case Node::TEXT_NODE:
1397 case Node::COMMENT_NODE: {
1398 auto& thisCharacterData = downcast<CharacterData>(*this);
1399 auto& otherCharacterData = downcast<CharacterData>(*other);
1400 if (thisCharacterData.data() != otherCharacterData.data())
1401 return false;
1402 break;
1403 }
1404 case Node::ATTRIBUTE_NODE: {
1405 auto& thisAttribute = downcast<Attr>(*this);
1406 auto& otherAttribute = downcast<Attr>(*other);
1407 if (thisAttribute.qualifiedName() != otherAttribute.qualifiedName())
1408 return false;
1409 if (thisAttribute.value() != otherAttribute.value())
1410 return false;
1411 break;
1412 }
1413 case Node::DOCUMENT_NODE:
1414 case Node::DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE:
1415 break;
1416 }
1417
1418 Node* child = firstChild();
1419 Node* otherChild = other->firstChild();
1420
1421 while (child) {
1422 if (!child->isEqualNode(otherChild))
1423 return false;
1424
1425 child = child->nextSibling();
1426 otherChild = otherChild->nextSibling();
1427 }
1428
1429 if (otherChild)
1430 return false;
1431
1432 return true;
1433}
1434
1435// https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#locate-a-namespace
1436static const AtomString& locateDefaultNamespace(const Node& node, const AtomString& prefix)
1437{
1438 switch (node.nodeType()) {
1439 case Node::ELEMENT_NODE: {
1440 auto& element = downcast<Element>(node);
1441 auto& namespaceURI = element.namespaceURI();
1442 if (!namespaceURI.isNull() && element.prefix() == prefix)
1443 return namespaceURI;
1444
1445 if (element.hasAttributes()) {
1446 for (auto& attribute : element.attributesIterator()) {
1447 if (attribute.namespaceURI() != XMLNSNames::xmlnsNamespaceURI)
1448 continue;
1449
1450 if ((prefix.isNull() && attribute.prefix().isNull() && attribute.localName() == xmlnsAtom()) || (attribute.prefix() == xmlnsAtom() && attribute.localName() == prefix)) {
1451 auto& result = attribute.value();
1452 return result.isEmpty() ? nullAtom() : result;
1453 }
1454 }
1455 }
1456 auto* parent = node.parentElement();
1457 return parent ? locateDefaultNamespace(*parent, prefix) : nullAtom();
1458 }
1459 case Node::DOCUMENT_NODE:
1460 if (auto* documentElement = downcast<Document>(node).documentElement())
1461 return locateDefaultNamespace(*documentElement, prefix);
1462 return nullAtom();
1463 case Node::DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE:
1464 case Node::DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE:
1465 return nullAtom();
1466 case Node::ATTRIBUTE_NODE:
1467 if (auto* ownerElement = downcast<Attr>(node).ownerElement())
1468 return locateDefaultNamespace(*ownerElement, prefix);
1469 return nullAtom();
1470 default:
1471 if (auto* parent = node.parentElement())
1472 return locateDefaultNamespace(*parent, prefix);
1473 return nullAtom();
1474 }
1475}
1476
1477// https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#dom-node-isdefaultnamespace
1478bool Node::isDefaultNamespace(const AtomString& potentiallyEmptyNamespace) const
1479{
1480 const AtomString& namespaceURI = potentiallyEmptyNamespace.isEmpty() ? nullAtom() : potentiallyEmptyNamespace;
1481 return locateDefaultNamespace(*this, nullAtom()) == namespaceURI;
1482}
1483
1484// https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#dom-node-lookupnamespaceuri
1485const AtomString& Node::lookupNamespaceURI(const AtomString& potentiallyEmptyPrefix) const
1486{
1487 const AtomString& prefix = potentiallyEmptyPrefix.isEmpty() ? nullAtom() : potentiallyEmptyPrefix;
1488 return locateDefaultNamespace(*this, prefix);
1489}
1490
1491// https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#locate-a-namespace-prefix
1492static const AtomString& locateNamespacePrefix(const Element& element, const AtomString& namespaceURI)
1493{
1494 if (element.namespaceURI() == namespaceURI)
1495 return element.prefix();
1496
1497 if (element.hasAttributes()) {
1498 for (auto& attribute : element.attributesIterator()) {
1499 if (attribute.prefix() == xmlnsAtom() && attribute.value() == namespaceURI)
1500 return attribute.localName();
1501 }
1502 }
1503 auto* parent = element.parentElement();
1504 return parent ? locateNamespacePrefix(*parent, namespaceURI) : nullAtom();
1505}
1506
1507// https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#dom-node-lookupprefix
1508const AtomString& Node::lookupPrefix(const AtomString& namespaceURI) const
1509{
1510 if (namespaceURI.isEmpty())
1511 return nullAtom();
1512
1513 switch (nodeType()) {
1514 case ELEMENT_NODE:
1515 return locateNamespacePrefix(downcast<Element>(*this), namespaceURI);
1516 case DOCUMENT_NODE:
1517 if (auto* documentElement = downcast<Document>(*this).documentElement())
1518 return locateNamespacePrefix(*documentElement, namespaceURI);
1519 return nullAtom();
1520 case DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE:
1521 case DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE:
1522 return nullAtom();
1523 case ATTRIBUTE_NODE:
1524 if (auto* ownerElement = downcast<Attr>(*this).ownerElement())
1525 return locateNamespacePrefix(*ownerElement, namespaceURI);
1526 return nullAtom();
1527 default:
1528 if (auto* parent = parentElement())
1529 return locateNamespacePrefix(*parent, namespaceURI);
1530 return nullAtom();
1531 }
1532}
1533
1534static void appendTextContent(const Node* node, bool convertBRsToNewlines, bool& isNullString, StringBuilder& content)
1535{
1536 switch (node->nodeType()) {
1537 case Node::TEXT_NODE:
1538 case Node::CDATA_SECTION_NODE:
1539 case Node::COMMENT_NODE:
1540 isNullString = false;
1541 content.append(downcast<CharacterData>(*node).data());
1542 break;
1543
1544 case Node::PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE:
1545 isNullString = false;
1546 content.append(downcast<ProcessingInstruction>(*node).data());
1547 break;
1548
1549 case Node::ATTRIBUTE_NODE:
1550 isNullString = false;
1551 content.append(downcast<Attr>(*node).value());
1552 break;
1553
1554 case Node::ELEMENT_NODE:
1555 if (node->hasTagName(brTag) && convertBRsToNewlines) {
1556 isNullString = false;
1557 content.append('\n');
1558 break;
1559 }
1560 FALLTHROUGH;
1561 case Node::DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE:
1562 isNullString = false;
1563 for (Node* child = node->firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
1564 if (child->nodeType() == Node::COMMENT_NODE || child->nodeType() == Node::PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE)
1565 continue;
1566 appendTextContent(child, convertBRsToNewlines, isNullString, content);
1567 }
1568 break;
1569
1570 case Node::DOCUMENT_NODE:
1571 case Node::DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE:
1572 break;
1573 }
1574}
1575
1576String Node::textContent(bool convertBRsToNewlines) const
1577{
1578 StringBuilder content;
1579 bool isNullString = true;
1580 appendTextContent(this, convertBRsToNewlines, isNullString, content);
1581 return isNullString ? String() : content.toString();
1582}

1584ExceptionOr<void> Node::setTextContent(const String& text)
1585{
1586 switch (nodeType()) {
1587 case ATTRIBUTE_NODE:
1588 case TEXT_NODE:
1589 case CDATA_SECTION_NODE:
1590 case COMMENT_NODE:
1591 case PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE:
1592 return setNodeValue(text);
1593 case ELEMENT_NODE:

1596 return { };
1597 case DOCUMENT_NODE:
1598 case DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE:
1599 // Do nothing.
1600 return { };
1601 }
1602 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1603 return { };
1604}

1606static SHA1::Digest hashPointer(const void* pointer)
1607{
1608 SHA1 sha1;
1609 sha1.addBytes(reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(&pointer), sizeof(pointer));
1610 SHA1::Digest digest;
1611 sha1.computeHash(digest);
1612 return digest;
1613}
1614
1615static inline unsigned short compareDetachedElementsPosition(Node& firstNode, Node& secondNode)
1616{
1617 // If the 2 nodes are not in the same tree, return the result of adding DOCUMENT_POSITION_DISCONNECTED,
1618 // DOCUMENT_POSITION_IMPLEMENTATION_SPECIFIC, and either DOCUMENT_POSITION_PRECEDING or
1619 // DOCUMENT_POSITION_FOLLOWING, with the constraint that this is to be consistent. Whether to return
1620 // DOCUMENT_POSITION_PRECEDING or DOCUMENT_POSITION_FOLLOWING is implemented by comparing cryptographic
1621 // hashes of Node pointers.
1622 // See step 3 in https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#dom-node-comparedocumentposition
1623 SHA1::Digest firstHash = hashPointer(&firstNode);
1624 SHA1::Digest secondHash = hashPointer(&secondNode);
1625
1626 unsigned short direction = memcmp(firstHash.data(), secondHash.data(), SHA1::hashSize) > 0 ? Node::DOCUMENT_POSITION_PRECEDING : Node::DOCUMENT_POSITION_FOLLOWING;
1627
1628 return Node::DOCUMENT_POSITION_DISCONNECTED | Node::DOCUMENT_POSITION_IMPLEMENTATION_SPECIFIC | direction;
1629}
1630
1631bool connectedInSameTreeScope(const Node* a, const Node* b)
1632{
1633 // Note that we avoid comparing Attr nodes here, since they return false from isConnected() all the time (which seems like a bug).
1634 return a && b && a->isConnected() == b->isConnected() && &a->treeScope() == &b->treeScope();
1635}

1637// FIXME: Refactor so this calls treeOrder, with additional code for any exotic inefficient things that are needed only here.
1638unsigned short Node::compareDocumentPosition(Node& otherNode)
1639{
1640 if (&otherNode == this)
1641 return DOCUMENT_POSITION_EQUIVALENT;
1642
1643 Attr* attr1 = is<Attr>(*this) ? downcast<Attr>(this) : nullptr;
1644 Attr* attr2 = is<Attr>(otherNode) ? &downcast<Attr>(otherNode) : nullptr;
1645
1646 Node* start1 = attr1 ? attr1->ownerElement() : this;
1647 Node* start2 = attr2 ? attr2->ownerElement() : &otherNode;
1648
1649 // If either of start1 or start2 is null, then we are disconnected, since one of the nodes is
1650 // an orphaned attribute node.
1651 if (!start1 || !start2)
1652 return compareDetachedElementsPosition(*this, otherNode);
1653
1654 Vector<Node*, 16> chain1;
1655 Vector<Node*, 16> chain2;
1656 if (attr1)
1657 chain1.append(attr1);
1658 if (attr2)
1659 chain2.append(attr2);
1660
1661 if (attr1 && attr2 && start1 == start2 && start1) {
1662 // We are comparing two attributes on the same node. Crawl our attribute map and see which one we hit first.
1663 Element* owner1 = attr1->ownerElement();
1664 owner1->synchronizeAllAttributes();
1665 for (const Attribute& attribute : owner1->attributesIterator()) {
1666 // If neither of the two determining nodes is a child node and nodeType is the same for both determining nodes, then an
1667 // implementation-dependent order between the determining nodes is returned. This order is stable as long as no nodes of
1668 // the same nodeType are inserted into or removed from the direct container. This would be the case, for example,
1669 // when comparing two attributes of the same element, and inserting or removing additional attributes might change
1670 // the order between existing attributes.
1671 if (attr1->qualifiedName() == attribute.name())
1672 return DOCUMENT_POSITION_IMPLEMENTATION_SPECIFIC | DOCUMENT_POSITION_FOLLOWING;
1673 if (attr2->qualifiedName() == attribute.name())
1674 return DOCUMENT_POSITION_IMPLEMENTATION_SPECIFIC | DOCUMENT_POSITION_PRECEDING;
1675 }
1676
1677 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
1678 return DOCUMENT_POSITION_DISCONNECTED;
1679 }
1680
1681 // If one node is in the document and the other is not, we must be disconnected.
1682 // If the nodes have different owning documents, they must be disconnected.
1683 if (!connectedInSameTreeScope(start1, start2))
1684 return compareDetachedElementsPosition(*this, otherNode);
1685
1686 // We need to find a common ancestor container, and then compare the indices of the two immediate children.
1687 Node* current;
1688 for (current = start1; current; current = current->parentNode())
1689 chain1.append(current);
1690 for (current = start2; current; current = current->parentNode())
1691 chain2.append(current);
1692
1693 unsigned index1 = chain1.size();
1694 unsigned index2 = chain2.size();
1695
1696 // If the two elements don't have a common root, they're not in the same tree.
1697 if (chain1[index1 - 1] != chain2[index2 - 1])
1698 return compareDetachedElementsPosition(*this, otherNode);
1699
1700 // Walk the two chains backwards and look for the first difference.
1701 for (unsigned i = std::min(index1, index2); i; --i) {
1702 Node* child1 = chain1[--index1];
1703 Node* child2 = chain2[--index2];
1704 if (child1 != child2) {
1705 // If one of the children is an attribute, it wins.
1706 if (child1->nodeType() == ATTRIBUTE_NODE)
1707 return DOCUMENT_POSITION_FOLLOWING;
1708 if (child2->nodeType() == ATTRIBUTE_NODE)
1709 return DOCUMENT_POSITION_PRECEDING;
1710
1711 if (!child2->nextSibling())
1712 return DOCUMENT_POSITION_FOLLOWING;
1713 if (!child1->nextSibling())
1714 return DOCUMENT_POSITION_PRECEDING;
1715
1716 // Otherwise we need to see which node occurs first. Crawl backwards from child2 looking for child1.
1717 for (Node* child = child2->previousSibling(); child; child = child->previousSibling()) {
1718 if (child == child1)
1719 return DOCUMENT_POSITION_FOLLOWING;
1720 }
1721 return DOCUMENT_POSITION_PRECEDING;
1722 }
1723 }
1724
1725 // There was no difference between the two parent chains, i.e., one was a subset of the other. The shorter
1726 // chain is the ancestor.
1727 return index1 < index2 ?
1728 DOCUMENT_POSITION_FOLLOWING | DOCUMENT_POSITION_CONTAINED_BY :
1729 DOCUMENT_POSITION_PRECEDING | DOCUMENT_POSITION_CONTAINS;
1730}

1732FloatPoint Node::convertToPage(const FloatPoint& p) const
1733{
1734 // If there is a renderer, just ask it to do the conversion
1735 if (renderer())
1736 return renderer()->localToAbsolute(p, UseTransforms);
1737
1738 // Otherwise go up the tree looking for a renderer
1739 if (auto* parent = parentElement())
1740 return parent->convertToPage(p);
1741
1742 // No parent - no conversion needed
1743 return p;
1744}

1808
1809void Node::showNodePathForThis() const
1810{
1811 Vector<const Node*, 16> chain;
1812 const Node* node = this;
1813 while (node->parentOrShadowHostNode()) {
1814 chain.append(node);
1815 node = node->parentOrShadowHostNode();
1816 }
1817 for (unsigned index = chain.size(); index > 0; --index) {
1818 const Node* node = chain[index - 1];
1819 if (is<ShadowRoot>(*node)) {
1820 int count = 0;
1821 for (const ShadowRoot* shadowRoot = downcast<ShadowRoot>(node); shadowRoot && shadowRoot != node; shadowRoot = shadowRoot->shadowRoot())
1822 ++count;
1823 fprintf(stderr, "/#shadow-root[%d]", count);
1824 continue;
1825 }
1826
1827 switch (node->nodeType()) {
1828 case ELEMENT_NODE: {
1829 fprintf(stderr, "/%s", node->nodeName().utf8().data());
1830
1831 const Element& element = downcast<Element>(*node);
1832 const AtomString& idattr = element.getIdAttribute();
1833 bool hasIdAttr = !idattr.isNull() && !idattr.isEmpty();
1834 if (node->previousSibling() || node->nextSibling()) {
1835 int count = 0;
1836 for (Node* previous = node->previousSibling(); previous; previous = previous->previousSibling())
1837 if (previous->nodeName() == node->nodeName())
1838 ++count;
1839 if (hasIdAttr)
1840 fprintf(stderr, "[@id=\"%s\" and position()=%d]", idattr.string().utf8().data(), count);
1841 else
1842 fprintf(stderr, "[%d]", count);
1843 } else if (hasIdAttr)
1844 fprintf(stderr, "[@id=\"%s\"]", idattr.string().utf8().data());
1845 break;
1846 }
1847 case TEXT_NODE:
1848 fprintf(stderr, "/text()");
1849 break;
1850 case ATTRIBUTE_NODE:
1851 fprintf(stderr, "/@%s", node->nodeName().utf8().data());
1852 break;
1853 default:
1854 break;
1855 }
1856 }
1857 fprintf(stderr, "\n");
1858}

1860static void traverseTreeAndMark(const String& baseIndent, const Node* rootNode, const Node* markedNode1, const char* markedLabel1, const Node* markedNode2, const char* markedLabel2)
1861{
1862 for (const Node* node = rootNode; node; node = NodeTraversal::next(*node)) {
1863 if (node == markedNode1)
1864 fprintf(stderr, "%s", markedLabel1);
1865 if (node == markedNode2)
1866 fprintf(stderr, "%s", markedLabel2);
1867
1868 StringBuilder indent;
1869 indent.append(baseIndent);
1870 for (const Node* tmpNode = node; tmpNode && tmpNode != rootNode; tmpNode = tmpNode->parentOrShadowHostNode())
1871 indent.append('\t');
1872 fprintf(stderr, "%s", indent.toString().utf8().data());
1873 node->showNode();
1874 indent.append('\t');
1875 if (!node->isShadowRoot()) {
1876 if (ShadowRoot* shadowRoot = node->shadowRoot())
1877 traverseTreeAndMark(indent.toString(), shadowRoot, markedNode1, markedLabel1, markedNode2, markedLabel2);
1878 }
1879 }
1880}
1881
1882void Node::showTreeAndMark(const Node* markedNode1, const char* markedLabel1, const Node* markedNode2, const char* markedLabel2) const
1883{
1884 const Node* rootNode;
1885 const Node* node = this;
1886 while (node->parentOrShadowHostNode() && !node->hasTagName(bodyTag))
1887 node = node->parentOrShadowHostNode();
1888 rootNode = node;
1889
1890 String startingIndent;
1891 traverseTreeAndMark(startingIndent, rootNode, markedNode1, markedLabel1, markedNode2, markedLabel2);
1892}

1902static void showSubTreeAcrossFrame(const Node* node, const Node* markedNode, const String& indent)
1903{
1904 if (node == markedNode)
1905 fputs("*", stderr);
1906 fputs(indent.utf8().data(), stderr);
1907 node->showNode();
1908 if (!node->isShadowRoot()) {
1909 if (node->isFrameOwnerElement())
1910 showSubTreeAcrossFrame(static_cast<const HTMLFrameOwnerElement*>(node)->contentDocument(), markedNode, indent + "\t");
1911 if (ShadowRoot* shadowRoot = node->shadowRoot())
1912 showSubTreeAcrossFrame(shadowRoot, markedNode, indent + "\t");
1913 }
1914 for (Node* child = node->firstChild(); child; child = child->nextSibling())
1915 showSubTreeAcrossFrame(child, markedNode, indent + "\t");
1916}

1974template <typename MoveNodeFunction, typename MoveShadowRootFunction>
1975static void traverseSubtreeToUpdateTreeScope(Node& root, MoveNodeFunction moveNode, MoveShadowRootFunction moveShadowRoot)
1976{
1977 for (Node* node = &root; node; node = NodeTraversal::next(*node, &root)) {
1978 moveNode(*node);
1979
1980 if (!is<Element>(*node))
1981 continue;
1982 Element& element = downcast<Element>(*node);
1983
1984 if (element.hasSyntheticAttrChildNodes()) {
1985 for (auto& attr : element.attrNodeList())
1986 moveNode(*attr);
1987 }
1988
1989 if (auto* shadow = element.shadowRoot())
1990 moveShadowRoot(*shadow);
1991 }
1992}

1994inline void Node::moveShadowTreeToNewDocument(ShadowRoot& shadowRoot, Document& oldDocument, Document& newDocument)
1995{
1996 traverseSubtreeToUpdateTreeScope(shadowRoot, [&oldDocument, &newDocument](Node& node) {
1997 node.moveNodeToNewDocument(oldDocument, newDocument);
1998 }, [&oldDocument, &newDocument](ShadowRoot& innerShadowRoot) {
1999 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(&innerShadowRoot.document() == &oldDocument);
2000 innerShadowRoot.moveShadowRootToNewDocument(newDocument);
2001 moveShadowTreeToNewDocument(innerShadowRoot, oldDocument, newDocument);
2002 });
2003}
2004
2005void Node::moveTreeToNewScope(Node& root, TreeScope& oldScope, TreeScope& newScope)
2006{
2007 ASSERT(&oldScope != &newScope);
2008
2009 Document& oldDocument = oldScope.documentScope();
2010 Document& newDocument = newScope.documentScope();
2011 if (&oldDocument != &newDocument) {
2012 oldDocument.incrementReferencingNodeCount();
2013 traverseSubtreeToUpdateTreeScope(root, [&](Node& node) {
2014 ASSERT(!node.isTreeScope());
2015 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(&node.treeScope() == &oldScope);
2016 node.setTreeScope(newScope);
2017 node.moveNodeToNewDocument(oldDocument, newDocument);
2018 }, [&](ShadowRoot& shadowRoot) {
2019 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(&shadowRoot.document() == &oldDocument);
2020 shadowRoot.moveShadowRootToNewParentScope(newScope, newDocument);
2021 moveShadowTreeToNewDocument(shadowRoot, oldDocument, newDocument);
2022 });
2023 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(&oldScope.documentScope() == &oldDocument && &newScope.documentScope() == &newDocument);
2024 oldDocument.decrementReferencingNodeCount();
2025 } else {
2026 traverseSubtreeToUpdateTreeScope(root, [&](Node& node) {
2027 ASSERT(!node.isTreeScope());
2028 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(&node.treeScope() == &oldScope);
2029 node.setTreeScope(newScope);
2030 if (UNLIKELY(!node.hasRareData()))
2031 return;
2032 if (auto* nodeLists = node.rareData()->nodeLists())
2033 nodeLists->adoptTreeScope();
2034 }, [&newScope](ShadowRoot& shadowRoot) {
2035 shadowRoot.setParentTreeScope(newScope);
2036 });
2037 }
2038}
2039
2040void Node::moveNodeToNewDocument(Document& oldDocument, Document& newDocument)
2041{
2042 newDocument.incrementReferencingNodeCount();
2043 oldDocument.decrementReferencingNodeCount();
2044
2045 if (hasRareData()) {
2046 if (auto* nodeLists = rareData()->nodeLists())
2047 nodeLists->adoptDocument(oldDocument, newDocument);
2048 if (auto* registry = mutationObserverRegistry()) {
2049 for (auto& registration : *registry)
2050 newDocument.addMutationObserverTypes(registration->mutationTypes());
2051 }
2052 if (auto* transientRegistry = transientMutationObserverRegistry()) {
2053 for (auto& registration : *transientRegistry)
2054 newDocument.addMutationObserverTypes(registration->mutationTypes());
2055 }
2056 } else {
2057 ASSERT(!mutationObserverRegistry());
2058 ASSERT(!transientMutationObserverRegistry());
2059 }
2060
2061 oldDocument.moveNodeIteratorsToNewDocument(*this, newDocument);
2062
2063 if (!parentNode())
2064 oldDocument.parentlessNodeMovedToNewDocument(*this);
2065
2066 if (AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled()) {
2067 if (auto* cache = oldDocument.existingAXObjectCache())
2068 cache->remove(*this);
2069 }
2070
2071 auto* textManipulationController = oldDocument.textManipulationControllerIfExists();
2072 if (UNLIKELY(textManipulationController))
2073 textManipulationController->removeNode(*this);
2074
2075 if (auto* eventTargetData = this->eventTargetData()) {
2076 if (!eventTargetData->eventListenerMap.isEmpty()) {
2077 for (auto& type : eventTargetData->eventListenerMap.eventTypes())
2078 newDocument.addListenerTypeIfNeeded(type);
2079 }
2080
2081 unsigned numWheelEventHandlers = eventListeners(eventNames().mousewheelEvent).size() + eventListeners(eventNames().wheelEvent).size();
2082 for (unsigned i = 0; i < numWheelEventHandlers; ++i) {
2083 oldDocument.didRemoveWheelEventHandler(*this);
2084 newDocument.didAddWheelEventHandler(*this);
2085 }
2086
2087 unsigned numTouchEventListeners = 0;
2088#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
2089 if (newDocument.quirks().shouldDispatchSimulatedMouseEvents(this)) {
2090 for (auto& name : eventNames().extendedTouchRelatedEventNames())
2091 numTouchEventListeners += eventListeners(name).size();
2092 } else {
2093#endif
2094 for (auto& name : eventNames().touchRelatedEventNames())
2095 numTouchEventListeners += eventListeners(name).size();
2096#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
2097 }
2098#endif
2099
2100 for (unsigned i = 0; i < numTouchEventListeners; ++i) {
2101 oldDocument.didRemoveTouchEventHandler(*this);
2102 newDocument.didAddTouchEventHandler(*this);
2103#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS) && PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2104 oldDocument.removeTouchEventListener(*this);
2105 newDocument.addTouchEventListener(*this);
2106#endif
2107 }
2108
2109#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS) && ENABLE(IOS_GESTURE_EVENTS)
2110 unsigned numGestureEventListeners = 0;
2111 for (auto& name : eventNames().gestureEventNames())
2112 numGestureEventListeners += eventListeners(name).size();
2113
2114 for (unsigned i = 0; i < numGestureEventListeners; ++i) {
2115 oldDocument.removeTouchEventHandler(*this);
2116 newDocument.addTouchEventHandler(*this);
2117 }
2118#endif
2119 }
2120
2121#if ASSERT_ENABLED || ENABLE(SECURITY_ASSERTIONS)
2122#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS) && PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2123 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!oldDocument.touchEventListenersContain(*this));
2124 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!oldDocument.touchEventHandlersContain(*this));
2125#endif
2126#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS) && ENABLE(IOS_GESTURE_EVENTS)
2127 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!oldDocument.touchEventTargetsContain(*this));
2128#endif

2135static inline bool tryAddEventListener(Node* targetNode, const AtomString& eventType, Ref<EventListener>&& listener, const AddEventListenerOptions& options)
2136{
2137 if (!targetNode->EventTarget::addEventListener(eventType, listener.copyRef(), options))
2138 return false;
2139
2140 targetNode->document().addListenerTypeIfNeeded(eventType);
2141 if (eventNames().isWheelEventType(eventType))
2142 targetNode->document().didAddWheelEventHandler(*targetNode);
2143 else if (eventNames().isTouchRelatedEventType(eventType, *targetNode))
2144 targetNode->document().didAddTouchEventHandler(*targetNode);

2151
2152#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)

2155#endif
2156#endif // PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)

2158#if ENABLE(IOS_GESTURE_EVENTS) && ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
2159 if (eventNames().isGestureEventType(eventType))
2160 targetNode->document().addTouchEventHandler(*targetNode);
2161#endif
2162
2163 return true;
2164}

2223
2224EventTargetData* Node::eventTargetDataConcurrently()
2225{
2226 // Not holding the lock when the world is stopped accelerates parallel constraint solving, which
2227 // calls this function from many threads. Parallel constraint solving can happen with the world
2228 // running or stopped, but if we do it with a running world, then we're usually mixing constraint
2229 // solving with other work. Therefore, the most likely time for contention on this lock is when the
2230 // world is stopped. We don't have to hold the lock when the world is stopped, because a stopped world
2231 // means that we will never mutate the event target data map.
2232 JSC::VM* vm = commonVMOrNull();
2233 if (vm && vm->heap.worldIsRunning()) {
2234 Locker locker { s_eventTargetDataMapLock };
2235 return hasEventTargetData() ? eventTargetDataMap().get(this) : nullptr;
2236 }
2237 return hasEventTargetData() ? eventTargetDataMap().get(this) : nullptr;
2238}

2249 setHasEventTargetData(true);

2281template<typename Registry> static inline void collectMatchingObserversForMutation(HashMap<Ref<MutationObserver>, MutationRecordDeliveryOptions>& observers, Registry* registry, Node& target, MutationObserver::MutationType type, const QualifiedName* attributeName)
2282{

2284 return;

2430void Node::defaultEventHandler(Event& event)
2431{
2432 if (event.target() != this)
2433 return;
2434 const AtomString& eventType = event.type();
2435 if (eventType == eventNames().keydownEvent || eventType == eventNames().keypressEvent) {
2436 if (is<KeyboardEvent>(event)) {
2437 if (Frame* frame = document().frame())
2438 frame->eventHandler().defaultKeyboardEventHandler(downcast<KeyboardEvent>(event));
2439 }
2440 } else if (eventType == eventNames().clickEvent) {
2441 dispatchDOMActivateEvent(event);
2442#if ENABLE(CONTEXT_MENUS)
2443 } else if (eventType == eventNames().contextmenuEvent) {
2444 if (Frame* frame = document().frame())
2445 if (Page* page = frame->page())
2446 page->contextMenuController().handleContextMenuEvent(event);
2447#endif
2448 } else if (eventType == eventNames().textInputEvent) {
2449 if (is<TextEvent>(event)) {
2450 if (Frame* frame = document().frame())
2451 frame->eventHandler().defaultTextInputEventHandler(downcast<TextEvent>(event));
2452 }
2453#if ENABLE(PAN_SCROLLING)
2454 } else if (eventType == eventNames().mousedownEvent && is<MouseEvent>(event)) {
2455 if (downcast<MouseEvent>(event).button() == MiddleButton) {
2456 if (enclosingLinkEventParentOrSelf())
2457 return;
2458
2459 RenderObject* renderer = this->renderer();
2460 while (renderer && (!is<RenderBox>(*renderer) || !downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer).canBeScrolledAndHasScrollableArea()))
2461 renderer = renderer->parent();
2462
2463 if (renderer) {
2464 if (Frame* frame = document().frame())
2465 frame->eventHandler().startPanScrolling(downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer));
2466 }
2467 }
2468#endif
2469 } else if (eventNames().isWheelEventType(eventType) && is<WheelEvent>(event)) {
2470 // If we don't have a renderer, send the wheel event to the first node we find with a renderer.
2471 // This is needed for <option> and <optgroup> elements so that <select>s get a wheel scroll.
2472 Node* startNode = this;
2473 while (startNode && !startNode->renderer())
2474 startNode = startNode->parentOrShadowHostNode();
2475
2476 if (startNode && startNode->renderer()) {
2477 if (Frame* frame = document().frame())
2478 frame->eventHandler().defaultWheelEventHandler(startNode, downcast<WheelEvent>(event));
2479 }
2480#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS) && PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2481 } else if (is<TouchEvent>(event) && eventNames().isTouchRelatedEventType(eventType, *this)) {
2482 // Capture the target node's visibility state before dispatching touchStart.
2483 if (is<Element>(*this) && eventType == eventNames().touchstartEvent) {
2484 auto& contentChangeObserver = document().contentChangeObserver();
2485 if (ContentChangeObserver::isVisuallyHidden(*this))
2486 contentChangeObserver.setHiddenTouchTarget(downcast<Element>(*this));
2487 else
2488 contentChangeObserver.resetHiddenTouchTarget();
2489 }
2490
2491 RenderObject* renderer = this->renderer();
2492 while (renderer && (!is<RenderBox>(*renderer) || !downcast<RenderBox>(*renderer).canBeScrolledAndHasScrollableArea()))
2493 renderer = renderer->parent();
2494
2495 if (renderer && renderer->node()) {
2496 if (Frame* frame = document().frame())
2497 frame->eventHandler().defaultTouchEventHandler(*renderer->node(), downcast<TouchEvent>(event));
2498 }
2499#endif
2500 }
2501}

2535// It's important not to inline removedLastRef, because we don't want to inline the code to
2536// delete a Node at each deref call site.
2537void Node::removedLastRef()
2538{
2539 ASSERT(m_refCountAndParentBit == s_refCountIncrement);
2540
2541 // An explicit check for Document here is better than a virtual function since it is
2542 // faster for non-Document nodes, and because the call to removedLastRef that is inlined
2543 // at all deref call sites is smaller if it's a non-virtual function.
2544 if (is<Document>(*this)) {
2545 downcast<Document>(*this).removedLastRef();
2546 return;
2547 }
2548
2549 // Now it is time to detach the SVGElement from all its properties. These properties
2550 // may outlive the SVGElement. The only difference after the detach is no commit will
2551 // be carried out unless these properties are attached to another owner.
2552 if (is<SVGElement>(*this))
2553 downcast<SVGElement>(*this).detachAllProperties();
2554
2555#if ASSERT_ENABLED
2556 m_deletionHasBegun = true;
2557#endif
2558 delete this;
2559}

2644struct AncestorAndChildren {
2645 const Node* commonAncestor;
2646 const Node* distinctAncestorA;
2647 const Node* distinctAncestorB;
2648};
2649
2650template<TreeType treeType> AncestorAndChildren commonInclusiveAncestorAndChildren(const Node& a, const Node& b)
2651{
2652 // This check isn't needed for correctness, but it is cheap and likely to be
2653 // common enough to be worth optimizing so we don't have to walk to the root.
2654 if (&a == &b)
2655 return { &a, nullptr, nullptr };
2656 // FIXME: Could optimize cases where nodes are both in the same shadow tree.
2657 // FIXME: Could optimize cases where nodes are in different documents to quickly return false.
2658 // FIXME: Could optimize cases where one node is connected and the other is not to quickly return false.
2659 auto [depthA, depthB] = std::make_tuple(depth<treeType>(a), depth<treeType>(b));
2660 auto [x, y, difference] = depthA >= depthB
2661 ? std::make_tuple(&a, &b, depthA - depthB)
2662 : std::make_tuple(&b, &a, depthB - depthA);
2663 decltype(x) distinctAncestorA = nullptr;
2664 for (decltype(difference) i = 0; i < difference; ++i) {
2665 distinctAncestorA = x;
2666 x = parent<treeType>(*x);
2667 }
2668 decltype(y) distinctAncestorB = nullptr;
2669 while (x != y) {
2670 distinctAncestorA = x;
2671 distinctAncestorB = y;
2672 x = parent<treeType>(*x);
2673 y = parent<treeType>(*y);
2674 }
2675 if (depthA < depthB)
2676 std::swap(distinctAncestorA, distinctAncestorB);
2677 return { x, distinctAncestorA, distinctAncestorB };
2678}
2679
2680template<TreeType treeType> Node* commonInclusiveAncestor(const Node& a, const Node& b)
2681{
2682 return const_cast<Node*>(commonInclusiveAncestorAndChildren<treeType>(a, b).commonAncestor);
2683}
2684
2685template Node* commonInclusiveAncestor<Tree>(const Node&, const Node&);
2686template Node* commonInclusiveAncestor<ComposedTree>(const Node&, const Node&);
2687
2688static bool isSiblingSubsequent(const Node& siblingA, const Node& siblingB)
2689{
2690 ASSERT(siblingA.parentNode());
2691 ASSERT(siblingA.parentNode() == siblingB.parentNode());
2692 ASSERT(&siblingA != &siblingB);
2693 for (auto sibling = &siblingA; sibling; sibling = sibling->nextSibling()) {
2694 if (sibling == &siblingB)
2695 return true;
2696 }
2697 return false;
2698}
2699
2700template<TreeType treeType> PartialOrdering treeOrder(const Node& a, const Node& b)
2701{
2702 if (&a == &b)
2703 return PartialOrdering::equivalent;
2704 auto result = commonInclusiveAncestorAndChildren<treeType>(a, b);
2705 if (!result.commonAncestor)
2706 return PartialOrdering::unordered;
2707 if (!result.distinctAncestorA)
2708 return PartialOrdering::less;
2709 if (!result.distinctAncestorB)
2710 return PartialOrdering::greater;
2711 bool isShadowRootA = result.distinctAncestorA->isShadowRoot();
2712 bool isShadowRootB = result.distinctAncestorB->isShadowRoot();
2713 if (isShadowRootA || isShadowRootB) {
2714 if (!isShadowRootB)
2715 return PartialOrdering::less;
2716 if (!isShadowRootA)
2717 return PartialOrdering::greater;
2718 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2719 return PartialOrdering::unordered;
2720 }
2721 return isSiblingSubsequent(*result.distinctAncestorA, *result.distinctAncestorB) ? PartialOrdering::less : PartialOrdering::greater;
2722}
